rican president. His half-century-long teaching career at Berkeley included a front row seat for the Free Speech Movement and the most documented student revolt in popular history. Told with humour, insight, and humility, Crises and Compassion moves nimbly among weighty events and meaningful personal history, showing how "civility in intellectual exchange" came to be the guiding principle of a life of monumental experiences.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aCollege teacherszCaliforniazBerkeleyvBiography. 0aEconomics teacherszCaliforniazBerkeleyvBiography. 0aEconomistszUnited StatesvBiography. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077358649940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773586499423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773586499/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles